<font color="#FF0000">GENERAL COMMENT </font><br>
<tt>Thu Feb  6 20:24:50 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
I don't know why I am bothering with this, but just feel I must respond.  I left the country of Vietnam almost 27 years ago, but it has never left me.  I find this site brings back  both sorrow and anger.  I guess most of it is sorrow for all those who still can't deal with it.  I may be among them.  I think I am most sorrowful for those who are still so enraged, whether they are protestors, or veterans who feel they were somehow taken advantage of.  The fact is, the world was taken advantage of, and the fault lies on all sides.  I find this site to be a great sounding board for all, and hope it serves a good purpose.  I'll try to contribute more later.  One interesting comment was how the war was a &quot;mistress&quot; in a marriage.  Guess the same sort of applied here, but the &quot;mistress&quot; died when I stayed behind, and my wife went to the Gulf war.  We both have a better understanding today, than we did before.
<p><code>-- ghitt@xmission.com  (George Hitt) </code><p>


